The paper deals with the Maximum Bipartite Subgraph problem on geometric intersection graphs, which involves both computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity and approximability of the problem, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The authors also mention the Maximum Independent Set problem, which is a well-known problem in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper introduces the Maximum Triangle-free Subgraph problem, which is related to graph theory and falls under cs.GT (Graph Theory).
